Short ball on middle, Boult sways away from the line of the ball.

OUT! Finally India manage to end New Zealand's first innings. Shami is the one who finishes it up. He bowls one short and on outside off, Jamieson fetches the ball from outside off and goes for the pull. He fails to get it from the sweet part of the bat and ends up hitting it in the air towards square leg. Rishabh Pant calls for the catch and runs to his left. He keeps his eyes on the ball and takes the catch by diving forward. NEW ZEALAND BOWL OUT ON 235!
Full and around off to start from Southee, Shaw strokes it towards cover-point firmly.
Length ball around off, Shaw comes forward and keeps it out.
India are underway with a leg bye. Length ball on the pads, Shaw looks to flick but misses to get hit on the pads. The ball rolls towards square leg and they take a leg bye.
Agarwal gets off the mark now. A short of a length ball on the body, Agarwal hops and works it towards fine leg for a run.
FOUR! Classy! Southee bowls it slightly fuller and around off, Shaw comes on the front foot and shows the full face of the bat and drives it straight down the ground. Pure timing.
Length ball on middle, Shaw is solid in his defense.
Length ball around off and middle from Boult, Agarwal works it towards the leg side.
In the channel outside off, Agarwal makes a leave.
Good length ball around off, Agarwal looks to defend but the ball takes the inner half of the bat and goes behind square leg. Before the fielder can come across, the batters take two.
Good length ball outside off, Agarwal taps it towards point.

OUT! CAUGHT! Boult strikes in his first over. Agarwal fails once again. Good length ball outside off from Boult, it jags back in sharply. Mayank is late in getting his bat down in time as he gets rapped on the front pad. They appeal and the umpire raises the finger instantly. Agarwal starts walking and then looks at Shaw for some help but probably Shaw tells him to keep walking. Agarwal had wasted one review in the first innings and this time he does not take the risk.

Another appeal but it dies down quickly. Good length ball angled into the batter, Pujara looks to flick but misses to get hit on the pads. Probably too high and hence the appeal dies down quickly. 2 runs and a wicket from Boult's first.
Length ball outside off, Shaw makes a leave there.
Length ball on off, Shaw blocks it out off the back foot

FOUR BYES! Wayward and very wide down the leg side. Southee bowls an ill-directed bouncer down the leg side and Shaw evades it. Watling behind the wicket dives to his left and it goes past him and into the fence at fine leg.
Length and on off, Shaw drives it off the front foot and towards mid off.
Full and on off, Shaw plays it to point.
On a length and on off, Shaw keeps it out off the front foot.
Length ball angled away from the batter, Pujara makes a leave.
Full and on off, Pujara does well to keep it out off the front foot.
Length and on the pads, Pujara flicks it towards square leg and gets a single.
FOUR! Shaw just uses the pace of the bowler there. It is short and wide outside off, Shaw guides it off the back foot past point and gets a boundary.
BEATEN! Boult bowls a seam up delivery and around off, Shaw looks to defend it off the back foot but gets beaten on the outside edge.
Length ball down the leg side, Shaw looks to flick but misses it as the keeper dives down the leg side and takes the ball.

Huge shout for a caught behind. Southee looks excited, the New Zealand players look excited but the umpire stand calmly out there. Tim bowls on a length and outside off, Pujara goes for the poke without any footwork and the ball whizzes past the outside edge. There is some excitement in the New Zealand camp but nothing from the umpire.
Length ball on off, Pujara blocks it off the back foot.
Short of a length ball outside off, Pujara drives it through point and gets three as the fielder mops it up.
Another short of a length ball on off, Shaw cuts it through point and gets three as Tom Blundell from point hares behind the ball and fields it at deep point.
Length and on off, Pujara defends it off the front foot to the off side.
Full and on off, Pujara drives it off the inside half of the bat towards mid on.
Good length ball just outside off, Shaw blocks it off the back foot towards the off side.
Slightly fuller and around off, Shaw punches it towards covers.
Flicked for a couple! A length ball angled into the batter, Shaw flicks it towards deep square leg for a couple of runs.
Bouncer down the leg side! Shaw ducks under it.
Outside off on a good length, Shaw thinks to go after it but controls it in the end.
Shortish and just around off, Shaw keeps it out.
Length ball on off, Pujara defends it right under his eyes off the back foot.
Full and outside off, Pujara guides it to point off the back foot.
Short ball down the leg side and Pujara ducks under it without any fuss.
Full and on middle, driven towards covers by Pujara.
Length and on off, Pujara brings out the solid front foot defense and keeps it out to the leg side.
Full and on middle, Pujara plays it with a straight bat and drives it down the ground. The ball hits the stumps at the bowler's end and then deflects towards mid off.
Length ball on leg, Shaw looks to flick it but gets beaten and is hit high on the pads. There is an appeal but nothing from the umpire.
Full and outside off, Shaw drives it through covers and gets a single this time.
Length and on leg, Pujara flicks it towards mid-wicket.
Full and wide outside off, Pujara shoulders arms to it.
Full and around off, Pujara plays it off the back foot towards point.
Full and on off, Pujara drives it off the front foot towards mid off.

OUT! CAUGHT! Shaw falls in the trap. Southee gets his first. Tim bowls one short and targeting the body of Shaw. Prithvi there looks to go for the pull but is nowhere in a position to play at it. Still, he goes through with it and ends up getting a glove on it. The ball lobs towards the slip cordon where Tom Latham at second slip takes a dolly. India have lost both their openers in quick time.

Bouncer way down the leg side and it further keeps going away from the keeper. Watling does well to move to his left and make a half-stop. Had he not get his hands, it would've gone to the fence. Only a run.
Good length ball around off, Pujara is solid in his defense.
Bouncer just outside off, Pujara sways away from the line.
EDGY FOUR! Pujara wanted to leave it but extra bounce meant that he ended up guiding it towards third man. He manages to find the gap and get a boundary.
Full and on middle, Pujara looks to flick but the ball takes the leading edge and rolls towards covers.
Length ball on middle, Kohli works it towards mid-wicket.
Full and around off, Kohli plays it back to the bowler who fields it in his followthrough.
Length ball on off, Kohli keeps it out off the front foot.

BEATEN! VIRAT KOHLI PLAYS AND MISSES. Boult comes round the wicket and bowls one on a length around off, Kohli goes for a drive away from the body and gets beaten on the outside edge. The demons of England Tour of 2014 are haunting him here.
On a length and angled around off, now Kohli goes for a back foot defense and gets beaten once again on the outside edge.

FOUR BYES! Boult goes an extra mile here but it is down the leg side. Kohli goes for the flick and misses it. The keeper too cannot prevent the ball from going to the fine leg fence despite putting in a full length dive.
Full and on the pads, Pujara flicks it towards deep square leg. Boult from fine leg runs quickly and throws the ball to the keeper and they stick with just one.
In the channel outside off, left alone.
Full and around off, Kohli comes forward and keeps it out.
Length ball around off, Kohli once again plays a solid front foot defense.

FOUR! You do not bowl on the pads of these Indian batters. It is bread and butter for them. Southee does that and Kohli whips it firmly. The ball races away to the deep mid-wicket fence. The Indian skipper is off the mark in style.
Angled into the pads, Kohli looks to flick but misses.
Short of a length ball on off, Pujara defends it to the leg side but gets it off the gloves there.
Full and on off, Pujara defends it off the front foot there.
Short of a length ball on off, Pujara plays it to point.
Fuller in length and on off, Pujara drives it off the front foot towards mid off.
Short of a length ball once again, Pujara hops inside the crease and keeps it down on the pitch.
Fuller in length and around off, Pujara blocks it on the leg side off the back foot.
Full and outside off, further swinging away from the batter. Kohli makes a leave.
FOUR! That is Virat Kohli at its best. Full and outside off, Kohli leans into the drive and gets it through covers for a boundary. INDIA LEAD BY 51!
Length and outside off, Virat lets it be.

EDGY FOUR! It could have gone either way but Kohli is lucky that it lands in between the two fielders. Jamieson goes short and wide outside off, Kohli has a tentative poke at it. The ball flies off the outside edge and goes between third slip and gully and into the fence behind. Kohli made sure that he played it with soft hands.
Full and on middle, Kohli flicks it to mid on.
Length and outside off, Kohli lets the ball through.
Full and outside off to start the spell from de Grandhomme, Pujara pushes it towards point.
Good length ball around middle and leg, blocked.
Length ball on the pads, worked towards mid-wicket.
Outside off, Pujara makes a leave.
Good length ball around off, Pujara comes forward and keeps it out.
Landed around off on a length, Pujara keeps it out.
In the channel outside off, Kohli lets it go to the keeper.
Length and on middle, Kohli plays it towards square leg and looks for a single but is rightly sent back by his partner.
On a length and outside off, Kohli makes a leave.
Short and wide outside off, Kohli cuts it uppishly over point and gets a couple.
On a good length and outside off, Virat shoulders arms to it.
Full and on middle, Kohli pushes it off the front foot and to the right of Jamieson who fields it.
Short of a length ball on middle, Pujara tucks it towards deep square leg and gets a single.
Full and on off, Kohli drives it straight to short cover who fields it by diving to his right.
Full and on middle, Kohli drives it to mid on.
Length ball on off, driven to mid off now.
On a length and on off, Kohli defends it off the front foot.
Length ball on off, driven to covers off the front foot.
Full and on the pads, Pujara plays it to mid on.
Outside off, left alone.
Full and outside off, Pujara plays it to point off the front foot.
Length ball around off, Pujara makes a leave to the one coming back into him. Luckily the ball does not come that much into him to cause any trouble.
Length and outside off, Pujara lets it be.
Back of a length ball outside off, Pujara drops his wrists and leaves it alone.

OUT! LBW! Kohli's bad patch continues. First Kyle Jamieson then Trent Boult and Tim Southee. Now, Colin de Grandhomme joins the list to dismiss Virat Kohli in this series. De Grandhomme lands one a bit fuller and around off and gets it to jag back into the batter. Kohli is committed to defend it but the ball swings in enough to beat his bat and hit the pads. There is a huge appeal and the umpire gives the marching orders for Kohli. Virat starts walking before looking at Pujara who asks him whether he wants to review it but he says something and then keeps walking. Replays later show that it was a good decision to not review it as the ball was crashing into the leg pole. He had made a poor DRS call in the first innings and didn't do it this time around.
In the channel outside off, left alone.
Good length ball around off, Rahane keeps it out.
Good leave! It is on  a length and just outside off but Rahane has his stumps covered.
Full and around off, Rahane blocks it off front foot.
Length ball on off, pushed towards point.
FOUR! Driven nicely! Jamieson overpitches this outside off, Pujara leans into the shot and drives it through mid off for a boundary. He is looking solid once again.
In the channel outside off, Pujara leaves it alone.
Good length ball around off, pushed towards point by Pujara.
Full and on a length, Pujara plays it to mid-wicket.
Length ball on off, Pujara keeps it out comfortably off the back foot.
Length ball on middle, Pujara blocks it off the back foot.
Full and on off, pushed back to the bowler by Rahane.
Length ball on off, Rahane keeps it out off the back foot towards the leg side.
Outside off, Rahane makes a leave.
Length and on off, Rahane drives it to covers.
Outside off, Rahane makes a leave.
On a good length and on off, Rahane blocks it by coming right behind the line of the ball.
Short of a length ball on leg, Rahane tucks it towards fine leg for a single.
Short of a length ball on leg once again. Pujara tucks it towards short leg where the ball falls just short of him there.
Short ball on leg, Pujara ducks under it.
On off, blocked off the back foot now.
Another one on middle, Pujara defends it off the back foot.
Length ball down the leg side, Pujara is happy to let that go.
Full and on middle, Rahane flicks it to mid-wicket for a single.
Brilliant effort in the field there. Pujara drives this full ball straight down the ground. Williamson from mid off fields it as the batters cross for a single.
Length ball on off, defended off the face of the bat.
Outside off, Rahane makes a leave.
Outside off, Rahane does not fiddle with it.
Length ball on off, Rahane blocks it off the back foot.
Short of a length ball on off, Pujara runs it past point and gets a single.
Short ball on middle, Rahane is happy to duck under it.
Back of a length ball on off, Rahane pulls it through mid-wicket for a single.
Bouncer but down the leg side, Pujara lets it be.
Length ball on off, Pujara flicks it to deep square leg and gets a single.
Length ball down the leg side, Rahane lets it be.
Good length ball on middle, Pujara works it towards mid-wicket.
Fuller and around off, Pujara pushes it towards covers.
Outside off, left alone.
Angles one on the pads, Pujara lets it be. Watling moves to his left and collects the ball.
Now a bouncer on middle, Pujara has no issues ducking under it.
On the pads, Pujara looks to flick but misses to get hit on the pads. The ball rolls to fine leg and they take a leg bye.
Tries to bowl a bouncer but ends up bowling it down the leg side. Pujara lets it be.
Landed around middle on a length. Pujara keeps it out.
On the pads again, Pujara looks to tuck it around the corner but misses to get hit high on the thigh pad. The ball rolls to fine leg and a leg bye is taken.

Dropped! De Grandhomme spills a chance. Short and outside off, Rahane goes for the pull but ends up getting a top edge towards deep square leg. De Grandhomme comes ahead and settles under the ball. He gets both hands and fails to hold on. This can be a really costly let off. A run taken.
Bouncer again but for Pujara. Yes, Pujara. So, he ducks under it.
Good length ball around off, blocked.
FOUR! Down the leg side, Rahane looks to fend it off. The ball hits his gloves and races away to the fine leg fence.
Sharp bouncer! It is on middle, Rahane does well to fend it off his back foot.
Another bouncer and Rahane is hit on the gloves again. It is a well-directed one again. Rahane is on the back foot and hoping as he fends it off.
Length ball on the pads, Rahane keeps it out.

Another bouncer and it is again a good one. Rahane goes for the pull again but the ball hurries onto him and hits him on the grill of the helmet and rolls towards fine leg. A leg bye taken. Jamieson goes to the batsman and then asks if he is fine. Rahane shows thumbs up. The umpire checks with him too and Rahane once again says it's all good. He then probably sees the Indian physio wanting to come on and check if he is fine but Rahane has his hands up to stop him and tell that he is okay and is ready to continue.
Barrage of the bouncers continue. But this one is for Pujara. You know what he does, well, most of the times, sits under it.
Bouncer again! Rahane ducks.
Another one but this one is down the leg side. Rahane watches it go past him.
Short and outside off, Rahane is not gonna duck too much as he throws his bat at it. He slashes it over point. Blundell at deep point  does well to keep it out.
Another bouncer, Pujara ducks again.
Finally a length ball, Pujara pushes it towards point.
Another bouncer but Pujara sits under it once again.
Good length ball on middle, Rahane tucks it towards mid-wicket.
Another sharp bouncer, Rahane fends it off his gloves.

Ouch! The physio will definitely come out now. Jamieson goes for the bouncer once again to Rahane and Ajinkya dares to take him on. The ball hurries onto him and hits him flush on the grill and lobs towards backward point. This time he calls for the physio right away. He though manages to run to the other end first. A leg bye given.
Yes it is but not a sharp one! This is on middle, Pujara keeps it out off his back foot easily.
Good length ball around off, Pujara blocks it with soft hands.
Bouncer outside off, Pujara sways away from it.
Wagner bangs one to Rahane now. He once again looks to go after it but at the last moment lets it be.
Shortish and around off, Rahane keeps it out.
Shorter again, Rahane pulls it towards mid-wicket.
Another sharp bouncer and this time Rahane gets a stare too. Rahane does well to evade it though.
Pulls this one to fine leg for a single. Smiles exchanged between Rahane and Wagner this time.
In the channel outside off, left alone.
A slower bouncer, Rahane blocks it out nicely.
Back of a length ball on the body, Rahane keeps it out.
Length ball just outside off, Rahane pushes it towards point and thinks for a run but Pujara sends him back.
Short and on off, Rahane is solid in his back foot.
Another back of a length ball on middle, Rahane moves towards the off side and thinks to pull but lets it be at the end.

In the air... but safe. This is nasty stuff from the Kiwi bowlers. Jamieson bowls this shooter around off, Rahane hops and looks to fend. The ball hits the upper part of the bat and lobs towards point. The fielder quickly comes forward but the ball lands well short.
Bumper down the leg side left alone.
Full and on off, Pujara drives it towards Williamson at covers who parries it towards towards mid off. The batsmen cross ends.

OUT! DRAGGED ON! Wagner roars, it's a mighty one as he says, 'COME ON'. Rahane's struggle is over. He has been put off by the bouncers so all he is expecting is another bouncer. This one from Wagner does not rise much but Rahane has already moved in the position of playing a pull. He realizes the pull short is not on so he tries to help it to fine leg but ends up cannoning the ball onto the stumps off his pads. Brilliant stuff from Wagner. He kept bowling the bouncers and has finally got the reward.
FOUR LEG BYES! Wagner welcomes  Yadav with a bouncer on leg, Yadav misses his flick and gets it off his thigh pad toward the fine leg fence for a boundary.
Good length ball around off, blocked.
Shorter in length and around off, Yadav keeps it out.
Full ball on off, pushed back to the bouncer.
Bouncer angled in from outside off, Pujara sways away from the line of the ball.
On the pads on a good length, Pujara looks to flick but misses to get hit on the pads. The ball rolls to deep square leg and they change ends taking a leg bye.
Length ball around off, Yadav pushes it towards point.
Bouncer for Yadav. It is on middle but Yadav ducks.
Full and swinging in, Yadav looks to flick but misses to get hit on the pads. A mild appeal from Boult but he knows there was an inside edge.
Full and around off, Pujara drives it straight down the ground through mid off. But lack of timing means the ball fails to cross the fence at long off. Three is what the batters get.
Length ball on leg, Yadav pulls it to deep square leg for a single.
Short ball down the leg side, Pujara ducks and lets it be.
In the channel outside off, Pujara ducks under it.

Full toss on middle, Pujara whips it towards deep mid-wicket. The ball is racing towards the fence. Boult from fine leg runs till deep mid-wicket and pulls the ball before it can reach the fence. Total commitment from the speedster.
The batsman defends it from within the crease.

OUT! Goes through the defense of the best defensive Indian batsman! What a brilliant piece of bowling from Boult. He angles a length ball from outside off into the right-hander. Pujara tries to defend but the incoming ball sneaks through his defense and disturbs the woodwork behind. This is a huge blow for India. Pujara's fighting effort comes to an end. Wonder if he could've done anything to this peach from Boult.
Good length ball on off, Vihari keeps it out.
Full and angling into the pads, Vihari tucks it to square leg for a single.
Bouncer down the leg side, Yadav looks to pull but misses.
Fuller and around off, Yadav keeps it out.
Shortish and around off, Umesh defends it off his back foot.
Shortish and around middle, Vihari keeps it out.
On the pads, worked towards the leg side.
Bouncer now! Vihari sits under it.
FOUR! Short and wide outside off this time. Vihari is on the toes quickly and slams it through point for a boundary.
Shortish and around middle, Vihari keeps it out.
Full and on the pads, Vihari flicks it to the leg side.

OUT! BOWLED 'EM! Too good for a tailender there. Boult is just too good with the cherry in his hand. He comes round the wicket and angles it into the off pole, Yadav who is camping on the back foot is found wanting too much on this ball. In the end he decides to flick it to the leg side but is late in doing so. The ball sneaks between the bat and pad to crash into the off pole. India's sorry tale with the bat continues. New Zealand are once again dictating the terms here.
Full and on middle, Pant flicks it towards mid on and takes a quick run.
Back of a length ball on middle, Vihari keeps it out.
Delivers a length ball outside off from wide off the crease. Vihari has his stumps covered as he lets it go to the keeper.
Full and around off, Vihari  comes forward and keeps it out. Last ball of the day coming up.
Shortish and around off from Boult. Vihari comes forward and then goes back to keep it out.
Runs straightaway! Southee starts with a fuller ball on the pads. It swings in as Pant flicks it to fine leg for a couple of runs before the fielder from deep square leg can come to cut it across.
In the channel outside off, Pant makes a leave.
Good length ball around off, Pant comes forward and keeps it out.
Another good length ball around off, Pant clips it to deep mid-wicket for a run. The lead for India is 100 now.
Good length ball just outside off, Vihari moves to his off pole a hint and defends it out.
Good leave to finish the over. Southee bowls this outside off on a good length and makes it come back in. Vihari covers his stumps and shoulders arms, trusting the bounce and line of the delivery.
Boult starts with a bouncer outside off, Pant lets it be.
Length and on off, Pant works it to mid-wicket.
In the channel outside off, moving away after pitching. Pant leaves it alone.
Good length ball on the pads, tucked to mid-wicket.
Full ball on middle, Pant flicks it nicely but de Grandhomme at mid-wicket makes a fine stop to his left.
Bouncer to end the over. It is a good one too as it is on middle. Pant spots that early and ducks under it.
Southee begins his second over with a length ball outside off, Vihari does not fiddle with it.
FOUR! First boundary of the morning! Southee bowls this length ball outside off, Vihari comes forward and drives it through point for a boundary.
Outside off now, Vihari lets it be.

OUT! Strangled down the leg side and India lose Vihari early. A top catch from Watling. This is not a wicket-taking delivery but New Zealand won't mind. It is a length ball down the leg side, Vihari tries to glance it fine but ends up getting a tickle behind. Watling moves to his left and dives to take a very good catch with both hands.
Very full and around off, Jadeja pushes it to mid off.
Lands this one around off and makes it to move away. Jadeja initially thinks of playing at it but at the last moment lets it go. End of a successful over from Southee.
Beaten! Boult bowls this just outside off on a length, Pant fiddles with the line to get beaten.
Landed around off on a length, Pant pushes it back to the bowler.

OUT! CAUGHT! Another one bites the dust and the Kiwis have a perfect start to the morning. A good length ball outside off, just a hint of away movement. Pant looks to force it to the off side but ends up getting an outside edge. The ball goes behind and Watling accepts the catch easily. Pant's poor run with the bat continues. These are the times when India needs a knock from someone like Pant but he has thrown away another chance. India just 104 ahead.
Full and around off, Shami keeps it out.
Full and around off again, Shami flicks it uppishly towards mid on. The mid-wicket fielder gives it a chase and keeps it down to two.
Beaten! Length ball just outside off, jags back in sharply as Shami tries to push at it.
Full and on middle, Jadeja flicks it to deep mid-wicket for a run. Southee won't mind bowling the next 5 balls to Shami. 100 up for India.
Length ball on the pads, Shami tries to flick but misses to get hit on the pads. The ball rolls to fine leg and the batters run a couple of leg byes.

Back of a length ball on middle, Shami wanted to go for the slog initially but the ball came back in and Shami in the end tried to fend it off the back foot but ended but getting a blow on his shoulders.
Full and around off, Shami strokes it to mid off for a run.
Short and around off, Pant helps it towards mid on with a gentle pull. He calls for a quick run.
Full and just outside off, Shami strokes it to deep cover but Jadeja denies the single.

Bouncer aimed at the head of Jadeja. He takes the challenge on and goes for the pull but misses. Watling behind the wicket times his jump and collects the ball over his head. Certainly saved 4 important runs, did Watling for his side.
In the channel outside off, Jadeja flirts with it to get beaten.
Goes full this time, Jadeja pushes it to mid off.

Full and on middle, Jadeja flicks it to mid-wicket and takes a run. A couple of balls for Shami to survive. Not sure if that will be on Shami's mind though as he loves to use the long handle. Let's see what he does.
It's a defensive stroke! A full ball outside off, Shami pushes it to covers.
Jadeja goes for the single on the last ball this time as Shami works this length ball on middle to find leg.
Bouncer on middle, Shami pulls it with control to deep square leg.
Beaten! Way outside off on a length, Jadeja tries to play at it but misses.

Did that carry to Watling? No, just short. A length ball outside off, Jadeja once again flirts with it. This time he gets an outside edge and the ball goes behind. Watling dives to his left and tries to catch but the ball falls just short. It goes behind the slip cordon and a run is taken.

OUT! CAUGHT! Shami holes out! Not sure if it was the time for this shot but he is Shami and he can do whatever he wants when he has the willow in his hand. He tries to slog this length ball on middle over deep mid-wicket but ends up miscuing it as the ball takes the inner half of the bat. Blundell at deep mid-wicket, well inside the ropes pouches it with ease. Interestingly, Jadeja did not cross and it will be Bumrah who will face the last two balls.
In the channel outside off, Bumrah lets it be.
Another leave as Southee bowls this one slightly fuller but outside off.
Length and outside off, Jadeja cuts it through point but denies the run.
Good length ball on middle, Jadeja keeps it out.
Good length ball just outside off, Jadeja tries to push it towards the off side but misses.
Swing and a miss! Full and just outside off, Jadeja goes for an all mighty slog but fails to connect. Had he connected, it would've landed in Australia.

SIX! Connects this time and sends it sailing over long on for maximum. Can he smack a few more to take India closer to 150? A length ball around off, Jadeja powers it over long on for a biggie. Vital six runs.
Tries to get a run and retain the strike as he goes to squeeze this fuller ball to deep cover but misses. Bumrah to face the next over.
Survives the first ball as Southee bowls it wide outside off. An easy leave.
Full and just outside off, Bumrah lets it go to the keeper.
FOUR! Tickled fine and 4 more vital runs. Southee sprays down the leg side and Bumrah just helps it down to the fine leg fence for a boundary.
Goes full and just outside off, Bumrah looks to get bat on ball but is beaten as the ball tails away.
Play and a miss again! Full and just outside off from Southee again, Bumrah once again fails to put bat on ball. One more delivery to survive.
Not a great ball to finish as Southee bowls a high full toss. Bumrah negotiates it with ease to get through the over.

Call is for two and they will make it easily. A length ball around off, Jadeja looks to defend  but the ball takes the inner half and goes towards deep mid-wicket. Jadeja quickly calls for a couple and completes it.
Bouncer but it is down the leg side, Jadeja lets it go.

FOUR! The long on fielder is inside the ring and Jadeja pulls it over that fielder to bag another boundary. A length ball just outside off, Jadeja takes a step forward and lofts it over the mid on fielder for a boundary. The lead crosses 130 now.
Shortish and around off and middle, Jadeja keeps it out off his back foot.
Sprays the length ball down the leg side. Jadeja goes for the flick but misses.

OUT! RUN OUT! Excellent awareness from Williamson. A shortish ball around middle, Jadeja taps it on the leg side. He takes a step forward and seeing that Bumrah responds and takes off. Jadeja though sees that Boult is charging at the ball, he sends Bumrah back. Boult collects the ball and fires the throw at the bowler's end but he misses. However, Williamson collects the throw and whips the bails quickly to find Bumrah short. The umpire raises his finger straightaway and does not think of checking it with the umpire upstairs. INDIA END WITH 124.
Good length ball on middle, Latham looks to work it on the leg side but misses to get hit high on the pads.
Just behind good length and on middle, Latham keeps it out off his back foot.
In the channel outside off, shaping away. Latham shoulders arms.
This one is fuller and just outside off, Latham trusts his instincts as he covers his stumps and lets it go to the keeper again.
Another leave as this length ball moves away after pitching around off.
Beaten! This time Latham fails to control himself as he tries to play at this length ball just outside off. He misses as the shaping away ball beats his inside edge.
Blundell and New Zealand are away. A length ball down the leg side, Blundell flicks it to deep square leg for an easy run.
Latham is looking a bit itchy right now. A length ball outside off, he can easily leave it along but he goes after it away from his body, only to miss out.
In the channel outside off, he this time lets it go to the keeper.
FOUR! Latham picks up a boundary. A gentle short ball around off, Latham swivels and pulls it to deep mid-wicket for a boundary.
Outside off, left alone.
Outside off on a length again, Latham lets it be.
Length ball outside off, Coming in towards the off pole but not enough as Blundell makes an easy leave.
Fuller and angling into batter, Blundell looks to flick it but gets hit on the pads and the ball rolls towards the off side.
Outside off, Left alone.

NOT OUT! Latham survives there. Length ball on off, Blundell drives it through covers and calls for a couple. The batter go it too. Shubman Gill from covers runs behind the ball and fields it. He throws the ball towards the bowler's end where Jasprit Bumrah fails to collect it as Latham who is running to that end makes his ground. The umpire goes upstairs to check whether it is out or not and the big screen flashes it not out and Latham survives.
Full and outside off, Blundell lets it be.
Beaten! Length ball outside off, Blundell tries to force it to the off side but misses.
Good length ball outside off, Latham tries to leave it alone but the ball comes back in and Latham is late in pulling his bat away. He ends up getting a bottom edge towards the second slip.
On the pads, Latham flicks it to fine leg for a run.
Slightly behind good length and outside off, Blundell keeps it out.
Sprays down the leg side. Blundell looks to flick but misses.
FOUR! That is some shot from Blundell. He loves it there. Yadav bowls one outside off and Blundell stands tall as he punches it through covers for a boundary.
BEATEN! The ball is spitting venom here. Yadav bowls in the channel outside off and Blundell plays inside the line to miss it.

Length ball outside off, Latham lets it be. But Pant has got to do a lot as the ball keeps going away from him. He dives to his left full stretch but fails to get to the ball. For his good luck, Pujara keeps the eyes on the ball and collects it at first slip.
That is a cracker from Bumrah. Slightly shortish one which pitches on middle and moves away. Latham has to play at it. He does so but only to see the ball whistle past his outside edge.
Full and on middle, he flicks it to mid-wicket for a run.
Another couple.. A length ball around off, Blundell works it behind square leg  and calls for a couple.
Good length ball outside off, Blundell first thinks of playing at it but draws his bat away at the last moment.
Fuller and around off, Blundell keeps it out coming forward.
Length ball wide outside off, Latham makes a leave.
Good length ball outside off, Latham does not bother to play at it.
FOUR! That is hit powerfully. It is a short of a length ball outside off, Latham cuts it through point and fetches a boundary.
Outside off, Latham makes a leave.
Short ball on leg, Latham evades it.
Outside off, Latham plays it to point.
Short of a length ball on leg, Blundell plays it towards square leg for a single.
FOUR! Beautiful shot! Pleasing to the eye there. Full and outside off, Latham drives it on the up through covers and the ball races to the fence there.
Short ball outside off, Latham makes a leave. Pant behind the wickets does well to collect it.
Another short ball outside off, Latham sits under it.
Length and on off, Latham watches the ball closely as he shoulders arms to it.
Length and outside off, Latham makes a leave once again to see of the over.
Length ball but down the leg side, Blundell is happy to let that go.
Length and on off, Blundell taps it to point this time.
Length and on middle and leg, Blundell plays it to mid on off the back foot.
Length ball on off, Blundell defends it to point.
Outside off, Blundell keeps it out once again off the back foot.
Full and down the leg side, Blundell looks to flick it but misses it.
Bumrah changes his angle and tries a bouncer on the body. It does not rise much and Latham helps it to fine leg for a run.
Good length ball just outside off, it comes into the right-hander with the angle. Blundell looks to defend but ends up getting an inside edge onto the pads.

Dropped? Yes, replays confirm but the umpire gives it as byes. A good length coming in, Latham looks to defend but the ball comes back in sharply. It sneaks through the gap between his bat and pad and flies to the left of  the keeper where Pant goes for it and misses it. Replays show that there was a massive inside edge on it. Hard luck for Bumrah there.

Appeal for LBW but nothing from the umpire. A good length ball around off, Latham lets it go to the keeper. There is some excitement from the Indian fielders there but nothing from the umpire. Replays show that the ball clipped the back pad on its way to the keeper.

Another appeal! OHH! Huge shout for lbw and Indians are excited there. It is bowled on a length and jags back into the batter. Latham prods forward for a defensive push only to miss it and get rpped on the pads. The umpire does not give it in maybe the ball was doing too much there.

And again! Bumrah is bowling brilliantly here. Once again it is Latham who is in trouble. This time Bumrah bowls one on a length and around off, Latham looks to defend it but gets rapped on the pads. There is an appeal but nothing from the umpire. Replays show that Latham got a big inside edge on it.
Short and on off, Blundell keeps it out.
Huge appeal but that is surely going down the leg side. Full and swinging in. Blundell looks to flick but misses to get hit on the pads. They appeal but not out says the umpire.

FOUR LEG BYES! Down the leg side, Latham looks to flick but misses to get hit on the pads. The ball goes behind and Pant throws himself to his right but fails to get to the ball and it then races away to the fence.
Shortish and around off, blocked.
Ouch!  A sharp bouncer from Shami. It is aimed at the head of Latham. He tries to evade it but the ball hits the grill and then his arms and rolls towards short fine leg.
Bouncer! Latham ducks to get through the testing over.

Just short! Bumrah bowls it fuller and outside off and draws Blundell forward. He goes for the drive only to get a thick outside edge. Kohli at second slip moves to his right to catch but it lands just short.
Slightly shorter and around off, Blundell blocks it off his back foot.
Play and a miss! Length ball just outside off, Blundell pokes at it to get beaten.
Around off on a length, Blundell hangs on the back foot and defends it out.
In the channel outside off, blocked.
Full and on middle, flicked to deep mid-wicket for an easy run.
FOUR! Timing is beautiful. Full and on middle, Blundell gets on the front foot and drives it to long on past the mid on fielder.
Length ball outside off, Blundell lets it be.
Length ball coming into the batter. Blundell looks to flick it but misses it to get hit high on the pads.
Length ball on off, Tom defends it off the back foot.

FOUR! He has played that with power. He has both his feet in the air as he plays this shot. It is a a short ball outside off, Blundell latches onto it as he cuts it uppishly over point and into the fence behind.
Full and on middle, pushed to the leg side for a run.
Good length ball around off, Latham blocks it towards point.
Outside off, left alone.
Wide outside off, Blundell reaches out and tries to punch but misses.
In the channel outside off, this time Blundell controls himself and watches it go to the keeper.
He fails to control himself this time as he chases this length ball outside off again and once again he fails to connect.
Good length ball around off, blocked.
Good length ball around off, Latham clips it to deep mid-wicket and changes ends.
Shortish and around off, Blundell keeps it out.
Fuller and outside off, left alone.
Shortish and around off, Blundell taps it towards gully.
Good length ball around off, Blundell looks to defend but the ball takes inner half and rolls towards square leg. They take a quick single.
Bouncer on middle. Latham ducks under it.
Full and on middle, flicked to deep square leg for a run.
Good length ball around off, blocked by Latham off the front foot.
Landed on a length and around the leg pole, Latham looks to nudge towards the leg side but misses to get hit on the pads. The ball rolls towards mid-wicket and they take a leg bye.
Good length ball around off, blocked.
Full and around off, Blundell drives it towards mid off where Vihari makes a fine stop with a dive to his right.
Shortish and around off and middle, Blundell pushes it towards mid-wicket for a single off his back foot. THAT IS LUNCH ON DAY 3.
A full ball on middle to begin, Blundell easily flicks it to wide of the man at mid on. Easy single.
Length ball around off, Latham keeps it out.
FOUR! Driven down the ground! A length ball around off, Latham shows full face of the bat and strokes it down the ground. The ball races away to the long off fence. 50 up for New Zealand.
Bouncer now but is way over. Latham ducks.
Length ball shaping away after pitching around middle and off, Latham lets it be.
Shortish and around off, Latham guides it towards the man at gully.
Shortish and around off and middle, Latham pushes it to mid off.
Length ball outside off, punched to mid off.
Another length ball around off, Blundell dabs it down through point for an easy run.
Landed on middle and leg on a good length, Latham works it towards mid-wicket.
Another ball which is on the pads, Latham looks to work it on the leg side but gets hit high on the thigh pad. The ball drops square of the wicket at that side and they steal a leg bye.
A couple to end the over! A length ball on middle and off, Blundell clips it towards deep mid-wicket for a couple of runs.
EDGY FOUR! Bumrah bangs it short and outside off, Latham looks to defend but the ball takes a thick outside edge and races away to the third man fence through gully.
Good length ball on middle, Latham looks to tuck it around the corner but the ball takes outer half of the bat and rolls towards the off side.
Landed on middle, Latham easily clips it to deep square leg for a run.
Shortish in length and angled into the batter. Blocked.
Another slightly shorter ball around off, Blundell guides it towards gully.
Good length ball around off, blocked.
FOUR! Pummeled! Short and around off, Latham swiftly moves inside and hammers it to the deep square leg fence.
FOUR! Another bouncer and Latham hammers it again. This is really poor from Yadav. He bowls another bouncer but it is not threatening at all. Latham this time pulls it to the fine leg fence.
Another ball on the pads, Latham works it to fine leg for a run.
On middle and leg, Blundell keeps it out.
Good length ball angled into the right-hander. Blundell looks to work it towards the leg side but ends up getting an inside edge on the pads.
Landed on a length on middle, Blundell tucks it towards mid-wicket. 9 from the over. 63 more needed.
Shortish and around off, Latham taps it onto the pitch on the off side.
On the pads from Bumrah now, Latham easily clips it behind square leg for an easy single.
Short of a length ball on off, Blundell keeps it out off the back foot.
Back of a length ball on off, Tom blocks it off the back foot towards the off side.
Short of a length ball on off, Blundell defends it off the back foot.
FOUR! Down the ground as New Zealand have done on many occasion in this series. It is bowled full and on middle, Blundell punches the ball through mid on and into the fence at long on.
FOUR! Latham welcomes Jaddu into the attack in style. Flatter and outside off, Latham rocks onto the back foot and punches the ball through point for a boundary.
Tossed up on off, Latham keeps it out off the back foot.
Full and on the pads, Latham plays it to the leg side.
Floated on off, Latham defends it off the front foot.
Good running between the wickets there. Flatter and outside off, Latham plays it through point and gets three as the man at dee point mops it up.
Full and on the pads, Blundell plays it towards square leg for a single. New Zealand need 50 more to win!
Good length ball around off, Blundell blocks it out.
Good length ball around off, Blundell pushes it towards point.
Shortish and around off again, Blundell is solid behind the line to defend.
Another slightly shorter one which is around off and middle, Blundell pushes it towards mid on.
Length ball on off, Blundell taps it to covers and shouts a loud 'wait on.
Short of a length ball on middle, Blundell keeps it out off the back foot to the leg side.
Floated ball on leg, Latham tucks it towards square leg for a run.
Tossed up on off, Blundell defends it to short leg.

SIX! Blundell has cleared his intentions here. Jadeja floats one on off. Blundell's eyes lit up as he dances down the track and lofts it cleanly over the bowler's head and into the fence at long off for a biggie.
Defended off the front foot by the batsman presenting the full face of the bat.
Comes down the track to this flatter ball and defends it out.
Floated around off, Blundell keeps it out.
Length and on middle, tucked to the leg side off the front foot.
Outside off, Latham makes a leave.
FOUR! Wow ! Glorious hit there. Yadav bowls on a length and on middle, Latham drives it off the inside half of the bat through mid on and into the fence at long on for a boundary.
Length ball on off, Latham defends it towards the off side.
BEATEN! Length ball around off, Latham goes for a poke on this ball but gets beaten on the outside edge.
Length ball on off, Latham keeps it out off the back foot.
Tossed up ball on off, Latham drives it to short cover.
Full ball on off, blocked off the front foot.
Outside off, left alone.
Floated ball on leg, Blundell plays it to the leg side.
Full and on off, driven to short cover once again.
Flatter and outside off, Blundell cuts it through point for a single.
Full and on off, Blundell pushes it off the back foot.
Length ball on off, tucked towards mid-wicket now.
FOUR! That's exquisitely played. Short of a length ball outside off, Blundell punches the ball off the back foot through point and fetches a boundary.
Length ball outside off, Blundell keeps the ball out to the off side off the outside half of the bat.

NOT OUT! Umpire's call there. Blundell survives. A good review there by India. Yadav bowls one on a length and on off, it comes a bit into the batter. Blundell goes for the defensive push but gets beaten and is rapped on the pads. There is an appeal from the bowler and his teammates. Kohli thinks about taking a review and then takes it finally. The replays roll in and first the  Ultra Edge comes on. It shows that there is daylight as the ball passes the bat. Now comes the Ball Tracker, it shows that the ball in pitching in line, the impact is also in line and then when it hits the stumps it is umpire call as it just clip the bails.
The batsman has punched the ball off the back foot.

FOUR! FIFTY FOR Latham. Batted brilliantly under pressure in the first innings and has done the same in this small run chase. Jadeja bowls it shorter one on middle, Latham hammers it via pull to deep mid-wicket. 100-run stand for the opening wicket.
On the pads, tucked behind square leg for a run.
Floated around off, it turns away after pitching to beat the outside edge.
Tossed up ball on off, Blundell comes forward and defends it out.
On off, it is defended.
Bowls a shorter one around off, Blundell goes on the back foot and keeps it out.
Shorter one on the pads, Latham looks to flick but misses to get hit on the pads.
Good length ball on off, pushed to point.
Good length ball outside off, left alone.
Length ball on off, Latham plays it to covers.
Short ball down the leg side, Latham leaves it. The keeper too fails to collect it.

OUT! CAUGHT! Sharp catch from Pant down the leg side. A bumper from Yadav, Latham goes for the pull but fails to connect. The ball takes the gloves and loops behind. Pant does well to move to his right and throw his right hand up to gobble the catch. Latham walked straightaway. They check for the no ball but Yadav is fine. India avoid another 10-wicket hammering.
Length ball on off, pushed to covers by Tom.
Length and outside off, Blundell makes a leave.
FOUR! That is crunched! Full and outside off, Blundell drives it through covers for a boundary. It was banished as soon as it came.
Short of a length ball on off, Blundell taps it to point.
Back of a length ball on off, Blundell plays it off the back foot to mid on.
Length ball on off, Blundell plays it back to the bowler off the back foot.
Full on off, played back to the bowler off the front foot.
Length ball on middle, tucked towards square leg for a run.
Short of a length ball on off, Blundlell pushes it to covers.
Length ball on off, Tom plays it off the back foot.
Short of a length ball outside off, it comes back in a bit. Blundell there looks to defend it off the back foot. The ball sneaks between the bat and the body and also goes over the sticks.
Outside off, left alone.
FOUR! Full and outside off, Williamson defends  it off the back foot and the ball rolls through  gully and into the third man fence.
BEATEN! Length ball outside off, Kane drives it only to get beaten on the outside edge.
Outside off, left alone.
Length and on off, pushed off the back foot by Kane.
Short ball on middle, Williamson ducks under it.

OUT! CAUGHT! A jaffa! Bumrah bowls a short one on off, Kane Williamson looks to evade this one but fails to get his wrists out of the line of the delivery.  The ball also jags back into the batter there as it takes the gloves and lobs towards gully where Rahane takes the catch.  Williamson's poor series with the bat ends here. 20 more needed for a win for New Zealand.
Full and around off, Blundell keeps it out.
Another fuller one around off, Blundell is solid in his defense once again.
Angled into the pads on a fuller length, Blundell tries flicking but misses to get hit on the pads. An appeal follows but it dies down slowly.
FOUR! HALF TON FOR BLUNDELL! A short and outside off one from Yadav, Blundell goes on the back foot and slashes it through point to reach the landmark.
Good length ball around off, Tom guides it towards short third man.
Landed on a length and on middle, worked towards mid-wicket.
Length ball on off, blocked off the back foot by Taylor.
Full and on the pads, Taylor plays it towards mid-wicket and takes a single. It went off the pads there and the umpire gives it as a leg bye.
Length ball on off, Blundell looks to defend it but gets an inside edge onto the pads.
FOUR! Full and on off, driven through covers for a boundary.

OUT! BOWLED! India are not going down without a fight. Bumrah roars in delight there. He was the one who was constantly asking questions at the batters and finally he gets the reward. It is bowled on a length and on off, It is a nip backer as Blundell looks to defend it leaving a big gap between his bat and pad. The ball sneaks through that gap and hits the top of off pole to send it for a cartwheel. The umpire stops the batter as they check for the no ball. The replays roll in and it shows that Bumrah has some part of his heel behind the popping crease. The third umpire to be completely sure sees the replay a few more times and then gives the marching orders for Blundell.
Length ball on off, Nicholls defends it off the back foot.
Shortish and just outside off, pushed towards covers.
Fuller one on off and middle, Taylor flicks it to mid-wicket.
Good length ball around off, Taylor comes forward and keeps it out.
FOUR! Short and on middle, Taylor goes on the back foot quickly and hammers the ball via a pull shot to deep square leg. 7 more needed.
Fuller and around off, pushed towards mid off.
Good length ball on off, blocked.
Length ball outside off, Henry makes an easiest of the leave.
Short ball on off, Nicholls pulls it  uppishly towards mid on where it lands just short of the fielder.
Length ball on off, pushed to the cover region.
FOUR! Nicholls gives the charge on this length ball outside off and  hits it uppishly over point for a boundary.
Defended off the front foot by the batsman presenting the full face of the bat.
Outside off, left alone.
Floated on the pads, Taylor sweeps it towards fine leg for a single.
Floated ball on off, blocked.
Full on the pads, flicked to mid-wicket.
Flatter on off, defended.

NO BALL! Jadeja has overstepped here. He bowls it flatter and outside off, Nicholls goes for the cut but fails to do so as the keeper collects it and appeals. The bowler and the keeper looks the most excited of the lot but the umpire is unmoved. Kohli takes the review and the replays roll in. Hang on folks! Jadeja has overstepped here.
Shortish and on off, Nicholls keeps it out.
There is the winning run! Full and around off and middle, Nicholls forces it through mid on for a single. THE KIWIS WIN BY 7 WICKETS.
